{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents a globally-unique actor that can be used to isolate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"various declarations anywhere in the program."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GlobalActor","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that conforms to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GlobalActor"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol and is marked with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@globalActor"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute can be used as a custom attribute. Such types"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are called global actor types, and can be applied to any declaration to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specify that such types are isolated to that global actor type. When using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such a declaration from another actor (or from nonisolated code),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"synchronization is performed through the shared actor instance to ensure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mutually-exclusive access to the declaration."}]},{"text":"Custom Actor Executors","anchor":"Custom-Actor-Executors","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A global actor uses a custom executor if it needs to customize its execution","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"semantics, for example, by making sure all of its invocations are run on a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specific thread or dispatch queue.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{